0xEB1C6DD.name: CREATE_DRY_VOLUME

params.name: xMin
params.description: The min X component of the AABB volume where water does not affect the player.

params.name: yMin
params.description: The min Y component for the AABB volume.

params.name: zMin
params.description: The min Z component for the AABB volume.

params.name: xMax
params.description: The max X component for the AABB volume.

params.name: yMax
params.description: The max Y component for the AABB volume.

params.name: zMax
params.description: The max Z component for the AABB volume.

0xEB1C6DD.description:
Creates a volume where water effects do not apply.
Useful for preventing water collisions from flooding areas underneath them.
This has no effect on waterquads, only water created from drawables and collisions.
Don't create volumes when your local ped is swimming (e.g. use IS_PED_SWIMMING in your scripts before you call this)
